1
00:00:23,210 --> 00:00:25,290
Hey, Nedumaran.
- Leo?

2
00:00:25,933 --> 00:00:27,806
Yes.
- Hey, how are you?

3
00:00:27,893 --> 00:00:32,326
I am doing great. How are you?
- I am fine, as usual.

4
00:00:32,533 --> 00:00:35,966
Wonderful! It's been a long time
since we met. - Yes.

5
00:00:36,413 --> 00:00:38,526
Where did Chika go?

6
00:00:40,286 --> 00:00:41,246
Chika?

7
00:00:41,886 --> 00:00:43,206
I don't know
who you're talking about.

8
00:00:43,606 --> 00:00:46,086
Chika, Nedumaran.
You were friends, right?

9
00:00:46,233 --> 00:00:48,006
Did you forget?
- Hey.

10
00:00:49,134 --> 00:00:51,636
I don't remember anyone like that.
How would I forget then?

11
00:00:52,403 --> 00:00:54,443
You really don't remember Chika?

12
00:00:54,566 --> 00:00:57,806
Hey, I don't know.
- Chidambaram, Nedumaran.

13
00:00:58,673 --> 00:00:59,766
Did you forget him?

14
00:01:04,846 --> 00:01:07,006
The TV remote is not working.
That's why I asked you to come.

15
00:01:07,393 --> 00:01:08,526
Check it.
- Okay, sir.

16
00:02:20,243 --> 00:02:22,846
Chef, did you finish
the ice washing?

17
00:02:23,286 --> 00:02:24,606
Then, for Riya..

18
00:02:27,486 --> 00:02:29,366
Why do you look sad, Chef?

19
00:02:36,726 --> 00:02:40,486
Oh, what is this?
A test for the chef?

20
00:02:41,583 --> 00:02:43,166
You are not going to go anyway.

21
00:02:43,703 --> 00:02:45,326
Then, why are you looking at it?

22
00:02:47,163 --> 00:02:48,046
Chef?

23
00:02:50,566 --> 00:02:51,566
What are you waiting for?

24
00:02:51,763 --> 00:02:53,846
Inform them right away
that you are not coming.

25
00:02:57,886 --> 00:02:58,806
Okay, Chef.

26
00:02:59,286 --> 00:03:02,046
I came to see if the food is ready.
Is it ready?

27
00:03:02,806 --> 00:03:03,846
Follow up with Grace.

28
00:03:09,726 --> 00:03:13,326
Do only what you like, singer Aura.

29
00:03:34,019 --> 00:03:36,606
Riya, stop.
I said stop..

30
00:03:36,673 --> 00:03:38,235
Why are you behaving like this?

31
00:03:38,283 --> 00:03:40,406
Please don't ask me anything.
Just leave me alone.

32
00:03:41,153 --> 00:03:42,483
I don't understand.

33
00:03:42,593 --> 00:03:45,686
Everyone will obviously know
you are pregnant. Then what?

34
00:03:46,173 --> 00:03:50,166
Yes, Deepak, but I have to decide
where and when to say it.

35
00:03:50,732 --> 00:03:53,026
You have to decide it?
What do you mean by 'you'?

36
00:03:53,603 --> 00:03:56,643
Excuse me, we are pregnant.
Don't you understand that?

37
00:03:56,966 --> 00:03:58,686
That is what I am saying, Deepak.

38
00:03:58,993 --> 00:04:02,726
We. If you say 'we', you should
have asked me before deciding.

39
00:04:03,326 --> 00:04:06,846
Riya, it's not a big deal for you
to react like this, okay?

40
00:04:07,332 --> 00:04:08,409
Of course, Deepak.

41
00:04:08,506 --> 00:04:11,606
Whatever you do is never
wrong, isn't it?

42
00:04:12,366 --> 00:04:14,526
I can't do this.
Look here.

43
00:04:14,713 --> 00:04:17,726
I am already under work pressure.
Don't irritate me. Just shut up.

44
00:04:18,692 --> 00:04:21,286
What? Shut up?
Why don't you shut up?

45
00:04:22,873 --> 00:04:24,406
Mind your words, Riya.

46
00:04:27,685 --> 00:04:29,563
What do you think
of yourself, Deepak?

47
00:04:29,793 --> 00:04:32,363
If I repeat what you just said,
you ask me to mind my words?

48
00:04:32,486 --> 00:04:34,406
What the hell?
- Look here, Riya.

49
00:04:34,753 --> 00:04:38,793
Don't act. Before my alter ego
gets triggered, just shut up.

50
00:04:39,153 --> 00:04:41,006
Or else, I will do
something uncontrollable.

51
00:04:42,450 --> 00:04:44,530
Oh, you are threatening me now?

52
00:04:45,243 --> 00:04:49,006
It's not right for you to speak
this way, knowing my anger.

53
00:04:53,653 --> 00:04:56,693
Rajan, ask him
to get out of my resort.

54
00:04:57,553 --> 00:04:58,686
Riya, one minute, please.

55
00:04:59,173 --> 00:05:00,443
Sir..
- What the fuck?

56
00:05:02,206 --> 00:05:03,486
Sir. Just a minute.
- Wait.

57
00:05:03,773 --> 00:05:06,003
Who the hell are you?
Go away.

58
00:05:06,286 --> 00:05:08,006
He is the manager of this resort.

59
00:05:08,493 --> 00:05:10,286
Rajan, throw him out.

60
00:05:13,553 --> 00:05:17,086
Riya, calm down.
We are talking, right?

61
00:05:19,273 --> 00:05:22,206
Sir.
- Hey, who are you first?

62
00:05:23,206 --> 00:05:24,486
Just mind your business.

63
00:05:25,806 --> 00:05:28,686
Get him away right now!
- You're going overboard.

64
00:05:37,153 --> 00:05:39,553
Deepak, it's not just you.

65
00:05:40,683 --> 00:05:42,646
I would have done the same
if it was someone else.

66
00:05:43,926 --> 00:05:47,246
You told me to mind my business,
right? This is my business.

67
00:05:48,033 --> 00:05:50,126
Now just get out.

68
00:06:34,486 --> 00:06:37,843
Tell me, Mom.
- Vetri, are you busy? - Yes.

69
00:06:38,013 --> 00:06:39,126
What is the matter?

70
00:06:40,006 --> 00:06:41,166
That is..

71
00:06:42,112 --> 00:06:45,512
Selvi said she was going
to play, right? - Yes.

72
00:06:45,573 --> 00:06:49,566
Do you need money for that?
- No, Vetri.

73
00:06:50,446 --> 00:06:52,606
You know about our village, right?

74
00:06:53,046 --> 00:06:54,886
When Selvi plays,

75
00:06:55,326 --> 00:07:00,326
she would wear trousers
and shorts and play without a care.

76
00:07:00,606 --> 00:07:02,043
After seeing all that,

77
00:07:02,526 --> 00:07:08,086
I don't know how our
villagers will talk. I feel bad.

78
00:07:08,563 --> 00:07:11,286
Our reputation in the village
is already bad.

79
00:07:12,363 --> 00:07:17,163
I don't have the strength
to bear their words.

80
00:07:17,443 --> 00:07:20,886
Mom, what is this? Why are
you thinking so much for her?

81
00:07:21,566 --> 00:07:23,846
We know about my daughter.

82
00:07:25,083 --> 00:07:29,742
But, others will talk
about her by her dress.

83
00:07:29,790 --> 00:07:32,779
How can they judge
a girl just by her clothes?

84
00:07:32,827 --> 00:07:34,403
What are you saying?

85
00:07:34,893 --> 00:07:36,206
Let them talk whatever they want.

86
00:07:36,563 --> 00:07:38,126
Selvi will play, that's it.

87
00:07:38,363 --> 00:07:41,206
Hey, not for that.
What I am saying is.. - Mom, look.

88
00:07:41,803 --> 00:07:46,646
If we keep thinking about others,
we will lose our peace.

89
00:07:46,763 --> 00:07:50,723
We don't live for others.
Our life, our peace. That's enough.

90
00:07:50,853 --> 00:07:52,803
Whatever.
I don't think this is right.

91
00:07:54,486 --> 00:07:56,886
It's because of you
that I'm letting her play.

92
00:07:57,233 --> 00:07:59,403
I can't handle your stubbornness.

93
00:07:59,723 --> 00:08:03,126
Selvi has to play. Don't think
about anything else, that's it.

94
00:08:03,433 --> 00:08:07,653
Okay, you carry on. I will hang up.
- Okay, Mom.

95
00:08:18,043 --> 00:08:20,206
Sir.. Sorry, sir.

96
00:08:20,433 --> 00:08:23,486
I was on the phone and didn't
notice you. Sorry, Sir. - It's okay.

97
00:08:24,693 --> 00:08:27,366
But, what you said is right.

98
00:08:28,366 --> 00:08:29,686
What did I say, Sir?

99
00:08:30,286 --> 00:08:33,006
If we take a decision
thinking about others,

100
00:08:33,526 --> 00:08:35,846
you said that it is wrong.
You're right.

101
00:08:36,206 --> 00:08:38,366
Did you hear that?
That's right, Sir.

102
00:08:40,446 --> 00:08:43,606
Correct. But, to understand this..

103
00:08:45,446 --> 00:08:47,406
I don't understand why
it took so long for me.

104
00:08:48,213 --> 00:08:50,995
I don't know if I can speak as much
as you can understand, sir, but..

105
00:08:51,043 --> 00:08:52,486
That's all I can understand, Sir.

106
00:08:55,006 --> 00:08:57,883
Sir, no need.
- Come, get it. - Sir.

107
00:08:58,039 --> 00:08:59,498
I am not giving it for free.
- No, Sir..

108
00:08:59,547 --> 00:09:01,083
I am giving it
for your work Take it.

109
00:09:03,843 --> 00:09:05,006
Thank you, Sir.

110
00:09:33,803 --> 00:09:36,443
Hey, the cream hasn't boiled yet.

111
00:09:36,733 --> 00:09:38,363
Why are you pouring it so soon?
- Hey.

112
00:09:38,473 --> 00:09:41,483
I don't know what'll happen if they
find out I'm doing this for you.

113
00:09:41,563 --> 00:09:43,806
And yet you fault me.
Shut up and keep quiet.

114
00:09:44,326 --> 00:09:45,726
Okay, don't get angry.

115
00:09:46,766 --> 00:09:49,403
There is chocolate, right?
Melt it and put it inside.

116
00:09:49,513 --> 00:09:50,723
Why should I melt it?

117
00:09:51,193 --> 00:09:54,086
If you put it in, it will melt
- Hey, fool.

118
00:09:55,763 --> 00:09:59,206
Hey, I found
a new recipe and told you.

119
00:09:59,526 --> 00:10:01,406
Why are you messing it up?

120
00:10:03,006 --> 00:10:05,846
I am the chef today, I will cook
the way I want to. Just shut up.

121
00:10:06,926 --> 00:10:08,686
You shouldn't speak.
You should keep quiet.

122
00:10:09,486 --> 00:10:11,486
I'm helping you
and you're going overboard.

123
00:10:11,686 --> 00:10:13,086
You're advising the chef.
- Look there.

124
00:10:13,163 --> 00:10:14,366
What?
- Look behind you.

125
00:10:15,006 --> 00:10:16,606
Why are you here today?

126
00:10:18,036 --> 00:10:19,916
Oh, no..
Aishu, I don't know anything.

127
00:10:20,206 --> 00:10:21,606
He asked me for help.

128
00:10:22,033 --> 00:10:23,046
Superb.

129
00:10:23,523 --> 00:10:25,798
Get lost,
or I'll report you myself.

130
00:10:25,846 --> 00:10:28,606
Why are you talking like this?
Come closer.

131
00:10:28,843 --> 00:10:30,446
Just a minute.
- Aishu.

132
00:10:30,923 --> 00:10:32,206
I don't know anything.

133
00:10:32,323 --> 00:10:33,726
Please come.

134
00:10:34,213 --> 00:10:37,083
Aishu, I don't know anything. Don't
tell this to Nedumaran. - Please.

135
00:10:38,886 --> 00:10:39,926
What?

136
00:10:40,243 --> 00:10:43,926
You know Mr. Joji, right?

137
00:10:44,603 --> 00:10:47,206
He asked me to make
a special dish for his lover.

138
00:10:47,643 --> 00:10:48,606
Don't snitch on me.

139
00:10:49,046 --> 00:10:51,046
I also tried to make it.

140
00:10:51,693 --> 00:10:54,006
But, you will create problems
if I come inside.

141
00:10:54,366 --> 00:10:55,806
That's why I thought of this idea.

142
00:10:56,046 --> 00:10:58,246
I can't do all that.
First, get out of here.

143
00:10:59,013 --> 00:11:02,763
Don't say like. He is a poor guy.
- Poor guy?

144
00:11:02,913 --> 00:11:04,686
There's no one there for him.

145
00:11:05,523 --> 00:11:08,326
He just met the woman
whom he loved back in college.

146
00:11:08,566 --> 00:11:10,166
He has been alone for so many days.

147
00:11:10,526 --> 00:11:12,966
Now, his life is filled
with happiness.

148
00:11:14,446 --> 00:11:17,846
That's why I am trying
to do something for him.

149
00:11:18,206 --> 00:11:20,166
It's okay if I don't do
it with my own hands.

150
00:11:20,613 --> 00:11:23,486
I don't mind if someone
else does it on my behalf.

151
00:11:24,006 --> 00:11:24,886
What?

152
00:11:26,846 --> 00:11:27,926
What is there to think about?

153
00:11:28,406 --> 00:11:30,283
He is our Joji.

154
00:11:30,766 --> 00:11:32,283
Listen to me, don't do it.

155
00:11:32,363 --> 00:11:33,806
If you get caught, it's over.

156
00:11:37,663 --> 00:11:41,566
Look, if he does it,
it'll definitely be a mess.

157
00:11:41,683 --> 00:11:43,483
Oh, no, he's pointing at me.

158
00:11:46,486 --> 00:11:47,686
If you don't mind,

159
00:11:49,206 --> 00:11:51,206
will you do it for me?
- Oh.

160
00:11:51,406 --> 00:11:53,486
Were you plotting this for me?
- No.

161
00:11:53,623 --> 00:11:54,526
Not plotting.

162
00:11:55,203 --> 00:11:56,526
It's just a help.

163
00:11:58,126 --> 00:12:00,406
If you do it for me,
you will feel blessed.

164
00:12:04,083 --> 00:12:06,286
Okay, I will do it.

165
00:12:06,926 --> 00:12:09,246
Don't do it so reluctantly.

166
00:12:09,683 --> 00:12:11,046
Then, it won't taste good.

167
00:12:12,043 --> 00:12:15,006
When you do it,
do it with love.

168
00:12:20,646 --> 00:12:23,046
I will do it with love,
like you asked.

169
00:12:23,343 --> 00:12:25,766
Tell me.
- Hey, nerd.

170
00:12:26,303 --> 00:12:28,206
Come out.
- Go, sir.

171
00:12:28,383 --> 00:12:30,606
Dump this, bring it.

172
00:12:31,326 --> 00:12:34,046
I don't know what he said.
- Just loaf around.

173
00:12:36,323 --> 00:12:37,286
Lighter.

174
00:12:37,903 --> 00:12:40,055
Chef, haven't you started
the preparation? - No.

175
00:12:40,103 --> 00:12:41,646
I'm making a dessert, Chef.

176
00:12:42,286 --> 00:12:44,046
Do it fast. Time's running out.

177
00:12:45,603 --> 00:12:47,603
Where is the lighter?
- Order, sir.

178
00:14:23,486 --> 00:14:24,686
What dish is this?

179
00:14:25,606 --> 00:14:29,166
This is the flavour of a dish
that is not on our menu.

180
00:14:31,126 --> 00:14:32,686
That's right, Chef, yes.

181
00:14:33,326 --> 00:14:34,846
This is a new dish.

182
00:14:35,366 --> 00:14:38,086
I wanted to ask you
and add it to the menu. - Oh.

183
00:14:38,403 --> 00:14:39,646
Oh, okay.

184
00:14:51,406 --> 00:14:52,286
Wow!

185
00:14:54,123 --> 00:14:55,286
Extraordinary.

186
00:14:57,726 --> 00:15:00,926
It just makes
the taste buds come alive.

187
00:15:02,043 --> 00:15:04,246
Quite a surprise.
Extraordinary, huh.

188
00:15:05,886 --> 00:15:07,726
What is the name
of this dish, Chef?

189
00:15:09,286 --> 00:15:11,806
I haven't named it yet, Chef.
- Oh.

190
00:15:12,483 --> 00:15:14,806
Can I?
- Sure, Chef.

191
00:15:19,443 --> 00:15:21,963
You put it in the serving cup.

192
00:15:22,423 --> 00:15:25,083
Maybe you can sprinkle some
chocolate powder

193
00:15:25,526 --> 00:15:29,803
and you can name it
as 'Dark Choco Kheer'.

194
00:15:30,523 --> 00:15:33,246
How is it?
- Nice, Chef. - Thank you.

195
00:15:35,126 --> 00:15:37,366
You did great. Keep it up.

196
00:15:48,873 --> 00:15:51,726
Aishu, we would've been
doomed if we'd been caught.

197
00:15:58,633 --> 00:16:00,086
Oh, God!

198
00:16:02,086 --> 00:16:05,686
What did he name it?
- 'Dark Choco Kheer.'

199
00:16:06,793 --> 00:16:08,886
'Dark Choco Kheer.'

200
00:16:09,333 --> 00:16:12,493
It's good.
- Get lost from here.

201
00:16:13,806 --> 00:16:16,646
Okay, you bring it. Bye.

202
00:16:26,446 --> 00:16:29,243
Sir, we made it
despite many challenges.

203
00:16:29,363 --> 00:16:30,726
Please tell us how it is.

204
00:16:31,083 --> 00:16:34,123
My feedback is not important.
Let Padma come and say it.

205
00:16:35,086 --> 00:16:37,822
Don't I know how
Vetri's cooking is?

206
00:16:38,249 --> 00:16:40,544
Sir, I didn't cook this time.

207
00:16:41,343 --> 00:16:44,526
A great chef has cooked this.
- Who is that great chef?

208
00:16:44,966 --> 00:16:46,446
This guy.
- Hey.

209
00:16:47,646 --> 00:16:49,726
This chef. Chef Aishu.

210
00:16:51,326 --> 00:16:54,406
Then, you don't have to say it.
It will definitely be good.

211
00:16:58,843 --> 00:16:59,883
Hi, ma'am.

212
00:17:06,243 --> 00:17:08,326
Sir, you carry on. We will
be back. Thank you, ma'am.

213
00:17:08,406 --> 00:17:09,246
Thank you.

214
00:17:12,803 --> 00:17:13,886
What is this?

215
00:17:15,643 --> 00:17:19,286
Try it. You will like it.
- You also eat.

216
00:17:28,083 --> 00:17:30,966
Wow! It's delicious.

217
00:17:33,566 --> 00:17:36,646
I asked them to prepare it
specially for you.

218
00:17:40,606 --> 00:17:43,926
It's very tasty.
It's really good, Joji. Thank you.

219
00:17:44,633 --> 00:17:45,766
My pleasure.

220
00:17:48,646 --> 00:17:49,646
Padma.

221
00:17:50,780 --> 00:17:52,060
Even back in our college days,

222
00:17:52,223 --> 00:17:55,646
you used to follow the same
dressing style, right? - Oh.

223
00:17:55,886 --> 00:17:57,926
Do you remember all that?

224
00:17:58,766 --> 00:18:01,086
They say that you forget
everything when you grow old.

225
00:18:03,084 --> 00:18:04,244
Who has grown old?

226
00:18:05,443 --> 00:18:09,166
I am still a youth.
Forever young.

227
00:18:13,566 --> 00:18:15,283
Eat.
- Padma.

228
00:18:15,863 --> 00:18:17,246
Can I ask you something?

229
00:18:18,926 --> 00:18:20,886
Why don't we
go on a date tomorrow?

230
00:18:25,440 --> 00:18:26,320
What?

231
00:18:27,326 --> 00:18:31,246
Padma, I just asked.
- What did you just ask?

232
00:18:31,696 --> 00:18:33,536
Don't you know what to ask, Joji?

233
00:18:42,286 --> 00:18:43,286
You got scared?

234
00:18:46,446 --> 00:18:48,883
You will tell the truth only if
you are scared, right? - Then?

235
00:18:49,163 --> 00:18:52,366
Why wouldn't I be scared?
Don't I know about you?

236
00:18:53,143 --> 00:18:56,566
Oh, in a short while, I felt
as if I saw the old Padma.

237
00:18:59,206 --> 00:19:02,606
Even I feel like seeing him.
- The old Joji?

238
00:19:02,936 --> 00:19:03,926
Yes.

239
00:19:07,886 --> 00:19:12,246
I am 60 years old. I am old Joji.
I'm not new.

240
00:19:20,363 --> 00:19:23,326
Oh, no, Joji.
I have to go now, okay?

241
00:19:23,643 --> 00:19:26,846
I will wait for you tomorrow
morning. Don't forget. - Okay, bye.

242
00:19:32,046 --> 00:19:34,166
Sir, what is the result?

243
00:19:34,643 --> 00:19:38,606
Will Joji ever fail the exam?

244
00:19:41,126 --> 00:19:43,446
But, you got scared that it will
fail for a second there, right?

245
00:19:43,683 --> 00:19:45,246
Okay, leave it.

246
00:19:45,686 --> 00:19:47,366
She got used to scaring me

247
00:19:47,523 --> 00:19:48,966
and I got used to getting scared.

248
00:19:49,806 --> 00:19:51,483
Sir, what is this?

249
00:19:52,086 --> 00:19:54,443
You could have told her
what you feel now, right?

250
00:19:55,926 --> 00:19:57,086
Like you said,

251
00:19:57,606 --> 00:19:59,446
even if I had spoken up then..

252
00:19:59,886 --> 00:20:02,006
even if all this
had happened before..

253
00:20:02,646 --> 00:20:05,686
even if I had spoken
in front of her,

254
00:20:06,606 --> 00:20:08,366
my life would have changed.

255
00:20:11,246 --> 00:20:13,006
Time waits for no one.

256
00:20:14,166 --> 00:20:16,406
If you don't speak up
where you should speak,

257
00:20:16,806 --> 00:20:20,486
it will become
a longing eventually.

258
00:20:23,123 --> 00:20:26,046
You should never let that happen.

259
00:20:37,483 --> 00:20:39,486
Hey, why is he drinking like this?

260
00:20:40,406 --> 00:20:42,486
He advises us when we drink a lot.

261
00:20:43,583 --> 00:20:47,366
After all, a manager
asked me to get out.

262
00:20:48,286 --> 00:20:50,726
He thinks he is the owner.

263
00:20:51,326 --> 00:20:53,806
For those thoughts,
she is the reason.

264
00:20:55,006 --> 00:20:56,423
She is the one.

265
00:20:56,843 --> 00:21:00,846
In my life, no one has
ever told me to get out.

266
00:21:01,846 --> 00:21:05,366
But, today, right to my face..

267
00:21:06,517 --> 00:21:07,394
Shit.

268
00:21:08,646 --> 00:21:10,046
Hey, Deepak, leave it.

269
00:21:10,483 --> 00:21:13,646
I never thought you'd
drink like that and blabber.

270
00:21:14,686 --> 00:21:16,726
Yes..

271
00:21:17,646 --> 00:21:18,966
He made me lament.

272
00:21:19,406 --> 00:21:21,966
He made me lament.

273
00:21:22,726 --> 00:21:25,766
In front of my wife,
he insulted me.

274
00:21:28,086 --> 00:21:29,043
I just..

275
00:21:30,126 --> 00:21:31,723
It sounds crazy.

276
00:21:33,366 --> 00:21:37,406
I have never felt.. I have
never been ashamed like this.

277
00:21:37,923 --> 00:21:39,926
Leave it, don't feel bad.

278
00:21:41,806 --> 00:21:43,486
He will regret what he did.

279
00:21:44,383 --> 00:21:45,726
He won't regret it.

280
00:21:46,003 --> 00:21:48,486
But, I will make him regret it.

281
00:21:51,363 --> 00:21:54,203
He thinks I am an ordinary person.

282
00:21:59,966 --> 00:22:01,166
His name is..

283
00:22:02,593 --> 00:22:04,923
Rajan..

284
00:22:07,206 --> 00:22:09,606
You have touched the wrong person.

285
00:22:11,046 --> 00:22:14,726
I will show you what
I am capable of. Just wait.

286
00:22:15,963 --> 00:22:18,246
Just wait.

287
00:22:18,983 --> 00:22:21,566
Hey..
- Hey, what is this?

288
00:22:21,643 --> 00:22:22,766
Hey, Deepak.

289
00:22:27,186 --> 00:22:29,026
Dad.
- Come in, dear.

290
00:22:34,749 --> 00:22:37,189
Dad.
- Tell me, dear.

291
00:22:46,606 --> 00:22:47,669
Tell me, Aishu.

292
00:22:49,349 --> 00:22:51,109
It's nothing. Go and eat, Dad.

293
00:22:52,789 --> 00:22:55,989
No, dear.
I think I will skip it today.

294
00:22:56,366 --> 00:22:57,429
I don't want dinner today.

295
00:22:57,909 --> 00:22:59,349
Why? What happened, Dad?

296
00:22:59,586 --> 00:23:03,589
I don't want it..
I will just skip it today.

297
00:23:11,386 --> 00:23:13,426
Dad, I want to tell you something.

298
00:23:13,586 --> 00:23:17,189
Actually, I wanted to tell you
something. Sorry for interrupting.

299
00:23:17,269 --> 00:23:18,189
Come and sit.

300
00:23:21,843 --> 00:23:22,803
You know..

301
00:23:26,146 --> 00:23:29,309
Today, you cooked very well.

302
00:23:30,146 --> 00:23:32,746
I think this is the first time I am
saying this to you. Am I right?

303
00:23:35,269 --> 00:23:37,989
You have given me
a lot of confidence today.

304
00:23:39,106 --> 00:23:40,869
The dish that you cooked..

305
00:23:41,866 --> 00:23:44,589
It was more than I expected.

306
00:23:44,806 --> 00:23:46,789
It was just
out of the world. It was awesome.

307
00:23:46,886 --> 00:23:48,029
It was awesome.

308
00:23:49,246 --> 00:23:52,166
I am telling you honestly.
Do you know one thing?

309
00:23:52,789 --> 00:23:57,229
Even when I won the Master Chef
award, I never felt so happy.

310
00:24:00,269 --> 00:24:04,189
You are the reason I am
so, so happy today. Yes.

311
00:24:07,069 --> 00:24:08,429
My dear Aishu.

312
00:24:08,746 --> 00:24:11,349
You are ready
for the Master Chef competition.

313
00:24:12,549 --> 00:24:13,509
Yes.

314
00:24:15,789 --> 00:24:19,509
Your sister betrayed me.
She disappointed me.

315
00:24:20,226 --> 00:24:21,829
Since you are with me,

316
00:24:22,989 --> 00:24:26,669
I don't have to worry about
your sister or your future.

317
00:24:30,706 --> 00:24:31,709
I don't know.

318
00:24:32,149 --> 00:24:34,869
I thought many times
that I've raised you strictly.

319
00:24:35,589 --> 00:24:38,629
I told you not to do this and that.

320
00:24:38,946 --> 00:24:40,989
But, you gave me the answer.

321
00:24:42,749 --> 00:24:46,269
I feared I'd be humiliated
in front of everyone.

322
00:24:47,466 --> 00:24:52,789
But, you cooked a dish and made me
so proud in front of everyone.

323
00:24:54,309 --> 00:24:55,466
I am so proud of you.

324
00:24:57,909 --> 00:24:58,829
Thank you.

325
00:25:02,826 --> 00:25:05,069
You wanted
to tell me something, right?

326
00:25:07,589 --> 00:25:09,349
Nothing, Dad.
- Are you sure?

327
00:25:12,136 --> 00:25:15,789
Okay, dear, I will finish
another drink and sleep.

328
00:25:16,516 --> 00:25:19,909
I will sleep happily today.
With my heart full.

329
00:25:21,116 --> 00:25:22,109
Yes.

330
00:25:23,349 --> 00:25:24,869
Time to sleep.
Good night, dear.

331
00:25:26,586 --> 00:25:27,589
Great night, Dad.
